name: Time&Circle - #0018
description: In ancient China, the circle represents harmony, the balance of yin and yang, and the duality of nature. In Buddhism, the circle of Zen means emptiness and the universe. To understand the universe, people must clear their minds and only a person who is mentally and spiritually complete can draw a true circle. In Japanese Enso or circle in Japanese word strongly associated with zen. It symbolizes absolute enlightenment, strength, elegance, the universe, and the void, it can also symbolize the aesthetic in Japan, as an expression of the moment.
